1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,001
In this lesson, we will explore SEO strategies.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:08,200
In the beginner SEO lesson, we covered various steps to improve your site's SEO.

3
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:13,080
One of the main points we highlighted was that search engines like quality content, knowledgeable,

4
00:00:15,760 --> 00:00:18,760
reliable and trustworthy content.

5
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:21,980
Also remember to install and activate an SEO plugin such as Yoast, RankMath, SEMrush,

6
00:00:25,120 --> 00:00:28,120
All-in-One SEO or SEOPress.

7
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:31,320
This tutorial will delve into more techniques to drive organic traffic.

8
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:35,720
Number one, develop a content strategy and target specific search phrases for better SEO.

9
00:00:39,720 --> 00:00:42,720
A content strategy helps you plan and consistently create valuable content.

10
00:00:44,640 --> 00:00:47,640
Start by researching what your audience is searching for, using tools like Google Keyword

11
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Planner.

12
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Then, create content that answers their questions and solves their problems.

13
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:59,400
For example, if your site is about gardening, write blog posts about seasonal planting tips,

14
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:06,040
pest control and for example DIY garden projects.

15
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:11,040
Also remember to use your keywords naturally in your titles and the first 100 words of

16
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
your post or page.

17
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:18,760
Here are a few other tips to take into consideration when doing keyword research.

18
00:01:20,680 --> 00:01:23,680
Firstly, long-tail keywords.

19
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:26,640
When people search online, they often use specific phrases to find what they're looking for.

20
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,000
These are called long-tail keywords.

21
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:34,520
Instead of broad terms like 'healthy smoothies', long-tail keywords are more specific, like

22
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:40,400
'easy strawberry banana smoothie recipe.'

23
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:44,080
Long-tail keywords are specific phrases that have lower competition but higher intent.

24
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:49,480
By targeting these specific phrases in your website content such as blog posts or product

25
00:01:51,520 --> 00:01:54,520
descriptions, you can attract people who are looking for exactly what you offer.

26
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:59,200
To do this, research the specific phrases your audience uses.

27
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:03,440
Then include them naturally in your content.

28
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:06,280
Guard against repeating your target phrase too many times on a given page, as it can

29
00:02:07,440 --> 00:02:10,440
start sounding spammy and robotic.

30
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:13,240
This helps search engines understand what your pages are about, making it more likely

31
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:18,040
they'll show up in search results when somebody searches for those terms.

32
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:22,680
Secondly, Semantic search.

33
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:25,920
Imagine you want to find related terms and phrases to your main keywords, just like

34
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:31,240
looking for synonyms or related ideas.

35
00:02:31,240 --> 00:02:34,240
Tools like Google Keyword Planner, Ahrefs or SEMrush help you do this by showing what

36
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:40,080
words and phrases people often search for that are similar to your main keywords.

37
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:45,200
This way, you can use those related terms to improve your website's chances of being

38
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:49,280
found by search engines.

39
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:51,320
Thirdly, let's talk about Content gap analysis.

40
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:55,720
So what is Content gap analysis?

41
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:58,600
It is finding out what topics your competitors are talking about that you aren't.

42
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,680
By identifying the keywords they rank for on search engines, you can see which important

43
00:03:04,920 --> 00:03:07,920
subjects you're missing.

44
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:09,600
Then, you can create content about those topics to attract more visitors.

45
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:15,200
The next topic we would like to discuss is Site Structure and User Experience.

46
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:20,880
Site Structure involves organising your website's pages and content logically.

47
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:26,840
This organisation helps search engines like Google understand and index your site more

48
00:03:29,200 --> 00:03:32,200
effectively.

49
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:33,200
A well-structured site enhances user experience by making navigation easier, leading to higher

50
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:39,760
rankings, increased traffic and better conversion rates.

51
00:03:40,960 --> 00:03:43,960
A good site structure guides visitors and search engines helping them find and engage

52
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:49,520
with your content efficiently.

53
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:52,360
Your navigation menu structure should be clear, organised and easy to use.

54
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:58,320
Also, ensure navigation labels are intuitive so users immediately understand what each link

55
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:05,440
leads to.

56
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:06,440
Additionally, on most sites it's important to have a search box for users who prefer to

57
00:04:08,320 --> 00:04:11,320
perform a keyword search.

58
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:13,680
User experience is how visitors interact with your site.

59
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:17,280
Ensure your site is easy to navigate, that it loads quickly and looks good on mobile

60
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:22,320
devices.

61
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:23,320
For example, use a clean, simple design and clear menus and ensure all links work and

62
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:29,480
are accessible.

63
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:31,640
This leads to our third topic, Improving page load speed and mobile optimisation.

64
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:38,280
A mobile-friendly fast website is crucial for keeping visitors happy and ranking higher

65
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:43,520
in search engine results.

66
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:46,080
People like fast websites and since more than half of your website traffic will come from

67
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:50,240
mobile users, optimising your site for mobile is an important step for improved SEO.

68
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:55,920
Let's talk about how you can achieve better page load speed.

69
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:59,960
Compress images to reduce size and use browser caching to load pages faster for repeat visitors.

70
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:07,280
And then use tools like Google PageSpeed Insights to check your site speed and get specific

71
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:12,920
recommendations.

72
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:14,920
Here are a few other steps to consider concerning mobile optimisation.

73
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:19,680
Number one,

74
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:20,680
select a responsive theme that automatically adjusts to different screen sizes.

75
00:05:22,480 --> 00:05:25,480
Many themes in the WordPress Repository are labelled as mobile friendly.

76
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:29,440
Secondly, ensure your site's navigation is easy to use on a mobile device.

77
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:34,640
Use clear menus and avoid hover-only navigation as it doesn't work well on touch screens.

78
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:40,320
Thirdly, avoid intrusive pop-ups that can frustrate mobile users.

79
00:05:42,840 --> 00:05:45,840
And then lastly, regularly use tools like Google PageSpeed Insights or HubSpot's website

80
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:51,760
grader to check how well your site performs on mobile devices and get suggestions for

81
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:56,920
improvements.

82
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:57,920
Next, we move on to link building and having a backlink strategy.

83
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:05,040
Backlinks are links from other websites to your site.

84
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,000
They show search engines that your site is trustworthy.

85
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:12,160
Link building is acquiring hyperlinks from other websites to your own.

86
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:16,520
Here are a few tips you can implement.

87
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:19,280
Firstly, quality content.

88
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,840
Earn quality backlinks by creating content others want to share and link to.

89
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:26,840
Number two,

90
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:27,840
social media.

91
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:28,840
Also share your content on social media platforms to increase visibility and attract links.

92
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Another example could be guest posting on other people's sites.

93
00:06:36,640 --> 00:06:39,640
It is therefore a good idea to guest blog on reputable sites in your industry or collaborate

94
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:44,520
with influencers who can link back to your site.

95
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:47,480
Next, we move on to optimizing internal links on your site.

96
00:06:49,520 --> 00:06:52,520
Internal links are like sign posts within your website, guiding both visitors and search

97
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:57,360
engines to different pages.

98
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Imagine your website as a city and each page is a building.

99
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:04,600
Internal links are the roads connecting these buildings.

100
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:07,760
They not only help visitors navigate your site but also show search engines how your

101
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:12,520
content is related.

102
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:14,520
For example, if you are writing a blog post about healthy eating and mention vegetarian

103
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:20,400
recipes, you could link that phrase to another page on your site, specifically dedicated to

104
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:27,160
vegetarian dishes.

105
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:29,200
This way, you are not only making it easier for readers to explore related content but

106
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:34,200
also signaling to search engines that the linked page is important for that topic.

107
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:39,600
Finally, when creating content for your site, it is advised to generate human-made content

108
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:45,640
and not rely on AI to write everything.

109
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:48,520
AI is not meant to replace people in content creation.

110
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:52,280
It should merely assist and enhance the process by providing tools and support for more efficient

111
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:57,680
and creative outputs.

112
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:59,760
Human involvement is crucial for gathering, evaluating and verifying facts, always prioritizing

113
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:06,320
accuracy and fairness.

114
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:08,760
Create deep content that shows true thought leadership.

115
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:13,720
By consistently implementing these strategies, you will improve your site's visibility,

116
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:18,400
attract more organic traffic and establish your presence in search engine results.

